---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="SkanPay - QR Payment Gateway for In-Store Transactions"
  description="SkanPay helps merchants and payment partners support QR code payment experiences for in-store and mobile wallet transactions."
  activePath="/"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">QR payment gateway</p>
      <h1>QR payment infrastructure for in-store acceptance</h1>
      <p class="hero-copy">
        SkanPay helps merchants and payment partners plan QR code payment acceptance for physical checkout.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button primary" href="/contact/">Contact SkanPay</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="/qr-payments/">Explore QR Payments</a>
        <a class="button ghost" href="/beamcash-demo/">View BeamCash Demo</a>
      </div>
      <div class="trust-strip" aria-label="SkanPay focus areas">
        <div class="trust-item">
          <strong>01</strong>
          Merchant checkout
        </div>
        <div class="trust-item">
          <strong>02</strong>
          Wallet-ready QR flow
        </div>
        <div class="trust-item">
          <strong>03</strong>
          Partner integration support
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <aside class="hero-panel" aria-label="SkanPay platform overview">
      <div class="panel-header">
        <span>Platform overview</span>
        <strong>SkanPay</strong>
      </div>
      <div class="system-card">
        <div>
          <span>Acceptance channel</span>
          <strong>In-store QR code payment</strong>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span>Primary participants</span>
          <strong>Merchant, customer, payment app</strong>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span>Transaction states</span>
          <strong>Created, scanned, authorized, confirmed</strong>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span>Business focus</span>
          <strong>Merchant and payment partner readiness</strong>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="signal-grid">
        <div><span>Flow</span><strong>QR request</strong></div>
        <div><span>Status</span><strong>Readable</strong></div>
        <div><span>Audience</span><strong>B2B</strong></div>
        <div><span>Scope</span><strong>Gateway</strong></div>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">What SkanPay does</p>
        <h2>Organize QR payment acceptance around a clear operating model</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        Visitors should quickly understand the service scope, the QR checkout model, and the right next step.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid three">
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>Services</span>
        <h3>Merchant acceptance planning</h3>
        <p>Define how QR payment fits into checkout, onboarding, and support workflows.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>QR payments</span>
        <h3>Transaction flow clarity</h3>
        <p>Describe the payment request, scan, authorization, and confirmation states.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>Partners</span>
        <h3>Wallet and app participation</h3>
        <p>Frame where payment apps, wallets, and loyalty platforms connect to checkout.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section technical-band">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Where SkanPay fits</p>
      <h2>A practical layer between checkout and mobile payment experiences</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        SkanPay positions QR payment as an operational workflow, not just a code on the counter.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid three">
      <article class="card data-card">
        <span>Merchant</span>
        <h3>Checkout state</h3>
        <p>Clear payment status language for staff at the counter.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card data-card">
        <span>Customer</span>
        <h3>Scan and approve</h3>
        <p>A familiar mobile action connected to a visible request.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card data-card">
        <span>Partner</span>
        <h3>Integration boundary</h3>
        <p>Defined responsibilities for wallet, loyalty, or payment apps.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">What to expect</p>
        <h2>Focused information, no unsupported claims</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        SkanPay presents only the claims that can be supported, without invented customer logos, processor promises, or compliance language.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid three">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Who it is for</h3>
        <p>Merchants, payment apps, mobile wallets, and loyalty platforms.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>What it covers</h3>
        <p>QR acceptance, transaction flow, onboarding, and partner fit.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>What comes next</h3>
        <p>A direct business inquiry through support@skanpay.us.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section demo-entry">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">BeamCash sandbox</p>
      <h2>Show the payment workflow without using real payment data</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        The BeamCash demo gives prospects a controlled walkthrough of a QR checkout session, from merchant request to customer approval and merchant confirmation.
      </p>
    </div>
    <a class="button primary" href="/beamcash-demo/">Open Demo Walkthrough</a>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Next step</p>
      <h2>Bring QR payment conversations into focus.</h2>
      <p>Share the merchant, partner, or product details you want SkanPay to support and the team can follow up directly.</p>
    </div>
    <a class="button secondary" href="/contact/">Start a Conversation</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
